Class BaseImplementor

java.lang.Object
info.kgeorgiy.ja.dmitriev.implementor.BaseImplementor
All Implemented Interfaces:
Impler
Direct Known Subclasses:
Implementor
public class BaseImplementor extends Object implements Impler
The class allows you to generate valid code using the token class. Class implementing Impler. The class also contains a console interface.

    • implement

      public void implement(Class<?> token, Path root) throws ImplerException
      Description copied from interface: Impler
      Produces code implementing class or interface specified by provided token.

      Generated class' name should be the same as the class name of the type token with Impl suffix added. Generated source code should be placed in the correct subdirectory of the specified root directory and have correct file name. For example, the implementation of the interface List should go to $root/java/util/ListImpl.java

      Specified by:
      implement in interface Impler
      Parameters:
      token - type token to create implementation for.
      root - root directory.
      Throws:
      ImplerException - when implementation cannot be generated.

    • implImplement

      protected static void implImplement(Class<?> token, Path root) throws ImplerException
      Produces code implementing class or interface specified by provided token. It's implementation of Impler.implement(Class, Path) without checking arguments for null.
      Parameters:
      token - type token that will be implementation
      root - directory that will contain the class
      Throws:
      ImplerException - couldn't implement
      ImplerException - couldn't write, i.e. the IOException occurred
